Utilizing a removable, serialized sub-chassis the Nano pistol can be easily modified with replaceable grip frames and is simple to disassemble and maintain.

Various Mosin Nagants. I have 8 Mosins, 6 M91/30's, 1 all matching 1953 Hungarian M44, 1 Finn-matched 1942 Sako M39 (shoots ~1" 100yds, it is more accurate than I am that's for sure). My 91/30's are 3 Tulas (1931, 1940, 1944, the 44 is a barreled action with all parts, no stock) and 3 Izhevsks (1940-scout scoped, 1943-refurbished, 1943, original, unissued all matching). Prices given upon request.

1918 MkIII* ShtLE Enfield. This rifle is basically a sporter or restoration project waiting to happen. When I got this rifle, some hillbilly had done a piss poor job of sporterizing the stock. Asking $85.

Swiss K31, 7,5x55 (GP11), a nice 1941 mfg K31 rifle made by SIG, went through rearsenal and is in a beech wood stock. All numbers match, including stock. Rifle shows typical dings on stock due to rough drilling, but the stock looks better than many I have seen. Bluing is also a lil thin in several areas due to pretty typical heavy cleaning Swiss soldiers did. Asking $375

title: For Sale:  RWS 54 Air King Rifle- .177 cal with 4X32 Scope
postcontent:
Brand New in Box
A totally recoil-less, spring piston airgun seemed little more than a dream before the recent appearance of the Model 54. In order to realize this goal the engineers spent years experimenting with different systems until they created this mechanical marvel. Simple but durable, the 54 uses a floating action riding on rails to achieve a totally recoiless system that stands up to the pounding of our 1100 fps system. Not only does this arrangement prevent transmission of felt recoil to the shooter, it also permits the rifle to excel in the accuracy department. When the rifle is fired, the action moves back lightly within the stock, absorbing the recoil, and permitting the pellet to exit the barrel before any of the spring vibration affects its travel. This system dramatically improves the accuracy potential of this magnum air rifle, making it a first class choice for either long range pest control or the precise demands of field target shooting. This side lever cocking magnum rifle's other features include adjustable trigger, adjustable rear sight, scope rail, Monte Carlo stock with cheek piece and checkering, and an automatic safety.

title: For Sale:  Get a grip, people!
postcontent:
So many of these ads are getting out of hand.  We either have people trying to sell a used gun for a new or higher price, or people wanting to buy a quality gun for significantly less than its fair market value.  

Sellers:  Your guns are not made of gold!  And don't forget that the pending gun legislation was shot down several weeks ago.  Stop trying to sell Glocks and such for outrageous prices!!  And just because you installed some custom parts on your budget 1911 does not make it worth any more than a new one at Academy Sports.  If you're researching completed Gunbroker auctions to see what a particular type of firearm is selling for, you cannot take into account inflated prices during the recent buying frenzy.  That frenzy is gone.  You missed the boat on the high dollars if you didn't sell your gun in January or February.  

Buyers:  Stop placing ads trying to buy a quality pistol for $150-200.  Go to your local pawn shop and buy a crap Hi-Point or something if that's all you want to spend.  Nobody is going to sell you a good S&W, Ruger, Sig, etc for that amount of money.

We need to meet in the middle and start selling and buying firearms for a current fair market value, not some unrealistic figure.  It's ok to negotiate, but when most people see a whacked-out price, they just keep browsing and think that the seller/buyer is unrealistic and would be a waste of time to deal with.

postcontent:
This is a reliable and quality shotgun and I am sad to see it go. I am original owner and have only put 24 rounds through this shotgun.

This is a perfect "Zombie Apocalypse" firearm to have, 12 gauge is a very common round sold at just about all sporting goods stores. Most people in theory would be hoarding handgun and AR / AK ammo giving you the edge on availability. Besides how readily available the ammunition is, this shotgun is Inertia Driven meaning the kenetic energy from the round cycles the action (also reducing recoil slightly) - More on the Inertia Driven system below.

The ghost ring sights on this shotgun are some of the best sights I have used (I have carried guns in my profession for many years and have served as a weapons and tactics training instructor) they make for quick target acquisition and are very accurate.

The Benelli M2 is a 12 gauge Semi Automatic Inertia Driven Shotgun. Inertia Driven action uses the recoil energy to cycle the action. This eliminates all the problems associated with gas-operated systems, such as the necessity of frequent cleaning and the tendency gas-operated systems have for malfunctioning during adverse weather conditions. This is the definition of reliability. 

This gun holds 5+1 rounds

This Benelli M2 also comes with Chokes IC, M, F and wrench. No box or manual to go with this sale.

The MSRP on this Shotgun is $1549
